Shape RS and PR

BRA <- ne_states(
  country   = "brazil",
  returnclass = "sf"
)

sul_sf = BRA[BRA$name %in% c("Rio Grande do Sul","Santa Catarina","Paraná" ),]

# convert to data.frame 
sul_sp = sf:::as_Spatial(sul_sf$geom)
## Warning in showSRID(uprojargs, format = "PROJ", multiline = "NO"): Discarded datum Unknown based on WGS84 ellipsoid in CRS definition,
##  but +towgs84= values preserved
# polygons(sul_sp)
sul_df= fortify(sul_sp)

Convert coordinates to UTM

lat = st_data$lat
lon = st_data$lon
xy <- data.frame(ID = 1:(length(lat)), lon, lat)
coordinates(xy) <- c("lon", "lat")
proj4string(xy) <- CRS("+proj=longlat +datum=WGS84")
res <- spTransform(xy, CRS("+proj=utm +zone=22 +units=m +north ellps=WGS84"))
## Warning in showSRID(uprojargs, format = "PROJ", multiline = "NO"): Discarded
## datum Unknown based on WGS84 ellipsoid in CRS definition
coords_utm = as.data.frame(res)
st_data$lat_utm =  coords_utm$lat
st_data$lon_utm = coords_utm$lon

x_coord <- c(min(sul_df$lon_utm), min(sul_df$lon_utm),  max(sul_df$lon_utm), max(sul_df$lon_utm), min(sul_df$lon_utm))
y_coord <- c(min(sul_df$lat_utm),max(sul_df$lat_utm),max(sul_df$lat_utm),min(sul_df$lat_utm),min(sul_df$lat_utm))

sul_pol = cbind(x_coord, y_coord)


p = Polygon(cbind(x_coord, y_coord))
ps = Polygons(list(p),1)
sps = SpatialPolygons(list(ps))
seasons = unique(as.character(st_data$season))

The extended K function in space–time

RS

d0_all = data.frame()
nsimul = 10000

for(j in 1:length(seasons)){
  print(j)
sul_sbr = st_data %>% 
  dplyr::filter(season == seasons[j])

rs_pts = cbind(sul_sbr$lon_utm, sul_sbr$lat_utm)

# computes the k functions
rs_kf = stkhat(rs_pts, sul_sbr$days_sep15, sul_pol, c(0, 200), seq(0,400000,10000), seq(0, 200, 5))

# Computes the Standard error for space-time clustering
stse = stsecal(rs_pts, sul_sbr$days_sep15, sul_pol,c(0, 200),seq(0,400000,10000), seq(0, 200, 5))

# Monte-Carlo test of space-time clustering
D0_RS = stmctest(rs_pts, sul_sbr$days_sep15, sul_pol, c(0, 200), seq(0,400000,10000), seq(0, 200, 5), nsim = nsimul, quiet = T)

oprod <- outer(rs_kf$ks,rs_kf$kt)
st.D <- rs_kf$kst-oprod
d0 = st.D / oprod 
resid = st.D/stse


min_d0 = min(d0, na.rm = T)
max_d0 = max(d0, na.rm = T)
Pvalue = sum(D0_RS$t > abs(D0_RS$t0)) / nsimul
# Pvalue

d0_df = data.frame(d0)
d_df = data.frame(st.D)

colnames(d0_df) = c(seq(0,400000,10000))
colnames(d_df) = c(seq(0,400000,10000))
d0_df2 = d0_df %>% 
  mutate(time = seq(0, 200, 5)) %>% 
  gather(1:41,key = "space", value = "d0") %>% 
  full_join(
  
d_df %>% 
  mutate(time = seq(0, 200, 5)) %>% 
  gather(1:41,key = "space", value = "D_hat")) %>% 
    mutate(space = as.numeric(space)) %>% 
  mutate(season = seasons[j]) %>% 
  mutate(P_value = Pvalue) %>% 
  mutate(min_d0 = min_d0,
         max_d0 = max_d0,
         resil_h = max(unique(as.character(resid >2 | resid < -2)), na.rm = T))  
  

d0_all = d0_all %>% 
  bind_rows(d0_df2)


  }

write.csv(d0_all, "data/d0_all.csv")
d0_all = read.csv("data/d0_all.csv")

Monte carlo testing results

sp2 = d0_all %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(season) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(m_p = mean(P_value, na.rm =T)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(season, m_p))+
  geom_point(size = 3, position = position_dodge(width = 0.5))+
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0.05, linetype = 2, size = 1.2, color = "gray50")+
  scale_color_colorblind()+
  labs(x = "Harvest season", y = "P-value", color = "")+
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(seq(0,5, 0.2)))+
  # coord_flip()+
  theme(legend.position = "top")

myplots <- list()  # new empty list
k =1

for(i in 1){
  for(j in 1:length(seasons)){
  
  p1 <- d0_all %>%
    # dplyr::filter(state == states[i]) %>%
    dplyr::filter(season == seasons[j]) %>%
    dplyr::filter(d0 != is.na(d0)) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(time, space/1000, fill =d0))+
    geom_tile()+
    # ylim(0,100)+
    xlim(0,150)+
    scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Spectral")+
    labs(x = "Time (days)",
         y = "Distance (km)",
         fill = expression(D["0"]),
         title = seasons[j])
    

  myplots[[k]] <- p1  # add each plot into plot list
  k = k+1
  }
}
